`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The codebase's instancing pattern groups by type (one `InstancedMesh` per `grassType`). Three.js `InstancedMesh.count` can be set to render fewer instances without re-creating, but the max capacity (`args[2]`) is fixed at construction. The solution: track capacity as state, grow-never-shrink — only trigger a re-render when entities exceed the current allocation.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
