`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The grow-only InstancedMesh capacity pattern avoids expensive GPU buffer re-uploads on chunk unloads — only the `mesh.count` needs updating for fewer entities, not a full `InstancedMesh` rebuild. A separate `capacitiesRef` (mutable, no re-render) vs `typeCapacities` state (React-owned, drives JSX) is needed because `useFrame` runs outside React's render cycle.
